n separate artifacts according to the normal documentation.\n[thinking] \n[assistant-event] thinking_end\n[assistant-event] text_start\n[assistant] {\n[assistant]   \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n[assistant]   \"summary\": \"No extra test dependency or Docker image is concretely required; the artifact already depends on Schema Registry client, Kafka clients, Avro types, Guava, and Jackson. Meaningful in-process coverage is reachable, but Schema Registry interactions must be configured to use Confluent's mock registry rather than a real service.\",\n[assistant]   \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n[assistant]   \"agent_guidance\": \"For tests that configure or exercise Schema Registry-backed serde behavior, set the serializer/deserializer config `schema.registry.url` to a unique `mock://<test-scope>` value, or inject/use `MockSchemaRegistryClient` directly. Clean up mock scopes after tests with `MockSchemaRegistry.dropScope(...)` when using `mock://`. Do not require a running Kafka broker or Schema Registry container for unit coverage.\",\n[assistant]   \"risks\": [\n[assistant]     \"The artifact is a shared/base serializer module; concrete Avro/JSON/Protobuf serializers live in separate Confluent artifacts, so tests should focus on classes in `kafka-schema-serializer` rather than adding format-specific serializers just to drive behavior.\",\n[assistant]     \"Formatter classes reference Kafka tools APIs through a provided Kafka dependency; avoid centering coverage on formatter entry points unless local Gradle resolution shows those APIs are available.\"\n[assistant]   ]\n[assistant] }\n[assistant-event] text_end\n[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Clarifying serializer configuration**\\n\\nThe schema registry URL is defined in the code as a serializer config, not as an environment or system property. That seems acceptable. I wonder if I need to mention that no additio