\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"advisory_preparation\\\",\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"No extra test dependency or Docker image is concretely required; the artifact already depends on Schema Registry client, Kafka clients, Avro types, Guava, and Jackson. Meaningful in-process coverage is reachable, but Schema Registry interactions must be configured to use Confluent's mock registry rather than a real service.\\\",\\n  \\\"deterministic_setup\\\": [],\\n  \\\"agent_guidance\\\": \\\"For tests that configure or exercise Schema Registry-backed serde behavior, set the serializer/deserializer config `schema.registry.url` to a unique `mock://<test-scope>` value, or inject/use `MockSchemaRegistryClient` directly. Clean up mock scopes after tests with `MockSchemaRegistry.dropScope(...)` when using `mock://`. Do not require a running Kafka broker or Schema Registry container for unit coverage.\\\",\\n  \\\"risks\\\": [\\n    \\\"The artifact is a shared/base serializer module; concrete Avro/JSON/Protobuf serializers live in separate Confluent artifacts, so tests should focus on classes in `kafka-schema-serializer` rather than adding format-specific serializers just to drive behavior.\\\",\\n    \\\"Formatter classes reference Kafka tools APIs through a provided Kafka dependency; avoid centering coverage on formatter entry points unless local Gradle resolution shows those APIs are available.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0a43dfc45c82546e016a3b12abf314819695361a4b9701f93e\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1026, \"output\": 1023, \"cacheRead\": 35328, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 37377, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1782256287266, \"responseId\": \"resp_0a43dfc45c82546e016a3b129fee48