tself must still pass and must not be made green by skipping the native path or disabling native-image behavior.\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/fix-index-file-inconsistencies/SKILL.md:3:description: Fix graalvm-reachability-metadata PRs where final validateIndexFiles against current master fails because metadata index.json tested versions are in the wrong metadata-version bucket, duplicated across buckets, or stale after another index-changing PR landed. Use during PR review when an index-changing PR must be repaired and pushed instead of labeled human-intervention.\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/fix-index-file-inconsistencies/SKILL.md:13:and then continue the review. Do not label the PR `human-intervention` for\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/fix-index-file-inconsistencies/SKILL.md:67:`human-intervention`.\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:23:- A new version that reports zero dynamic-access calls (for example `dynamicAccess.totalCalls == 0`, or a `{}` `reachability-metadata.json` with no claimed dynamic-access behavior) does not give enough information to judge whether metadata is unnecessary or whether a metadata-entry-count drop is meaningful. Dynamic-access stats can miss metadata required through transitive dependencies. Do not report a metadata-entry-count drop, and do not flag a shallow test or a test that exercises behavior outside the library's responsibility, as a blocking issue or `human-intervention` for such a library. The Java runtime fix itself must still pass and must not be made green by swallowing the failure or disabling native-image behavior.\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/README.md:52:### `close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs`\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/README.md:54:Closes batches of open pull requests that have the `human-intervention` label or failing CI.\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:2:name: close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:3:description: Close batches of graalvm-reachability-metadata pull requests that either have the `human-intervention` label or failing CI, and revert their linked issues by clearing assignees and moving project status to `Todo`.\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:18:- The PR has the `human-intervention` label.\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:29:   - Fetch open human-intervention PRs:\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:31:     gh pr list -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --state open --label human-intervention --limit 200 --json number,title,url,labels,statusCheckRollup\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:150:     gh pr close PR_NUMBER -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --comment \"Closing this human-intervention PR and returning the linked issue to Todo.\"\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:183:- PRs closed for `human-intervention`\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:23:- A new version that reports zero dynamic-access calls (for example `dynamicAccess.totalCalls == 0`, or a `{}` `reachability-metadata.json` with no claimed dynamic-access behavior) does not give enough information to judge whether metadata is unnecessary or whether a metadata-entry-count drop is meaningful. Dynamic-access stats can miss metadata required through transitive dependencies. Do not report a metadata-entry-count drop, and do not flag a shallow test or a test that exercises behavior outside the library's responsibility, as a blocking issue or `human-intervention` for such a library. The compile fix itself must still pass and must not be made green by deleting meaningful coverage or disabling native-image behavior.\n../8564-c89a35b7/skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:18:- A requested version that reports zero dy